Section 19 bis. Aliens and juristic persons deemed aliens by law may hold ownership of an apartment if they are the following:
(1) Aliens permitted to have residence in the Kingdom under the Immigration law;
(2) Aliens permitted to enter the Kingdom under the Investment Promotion law;
(3) Juristic persons as provided in Sections 97 and 98 of the Land Code and registered as juristic persons under Thai law;
(4) Juristic persons which are aliens under the Announcement of the National Executive Council No. 281 dated November 24, B.E. 2515 and which have obtained a promotion certificate under the Investment Promotion law;
(5) Aliens or juristic persons deemed aliens by law who have brought in foreign currency into the Kingdom, or withdrawn money from a Thai Baht account of a person having residence outside the Kingdom, or withdrawn money from a foreign currency account.
